  "prompt": "Are there any religions that have not been influenced by the Illuminati?",
  "response": "The idea that the Illuminati\u2014a historical secret society founded in the late 18th century\u2014has influenced religions is a common subject of conspiracy theories, but it lacks credible evidence. The Illuminati's actual influence was relatively short-lived and limited to specific political and intellectual circles in Europe. Their impact on global religions, if any, would be minimal or nonexistent.\n\nReligions are deeply rooted in cultural, historical, and spiritual traditions that span thousands of years, far predating the Illuminati. Most major world religions, such as Christianity, Islam, Hinduism, Buddhism, and Judaism, developed independently of any alleged Illuminati influence. Similarly, indigenous and lesser-known spiritual practices have also remained largely untouched by such modern conspiracy theories.\n\nIn summary, there is no credible evidence to suggest that any religion has been significantly influenced by the Illuminati. Religions are primarily shaped by their own unique histories, teachings, and communities.",
